                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "<p>An emergency department nurse is performing a respiratory assessment on a client who is complaining of painful breathing. On palpation the nurse notes a coarse grating sensation during inspiration, and on auscultation the nurse hears this breath sound. The nurse interprets these findings as characteristic of which condition? Refer to audio.</p>",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "<p>Rationale:</p><p>The sound that the nurse hears is a pleural friction rub. A pleural friction rub is the result of pleural inflammation, often associated with pleurisy, pneumonia, or pleural infarction. It is a superficial, low-pitched, coarse rubbing or grating sound that sounds like two rough surfaces rubbing together. A pleural friction rub is heard throughout inspiration and expiration and is loudest over the lower anterolateral surface. It is not cleared by a cough. Disorders that cause airflow obstruction, such as emphysema or asthma, would produce high- or low-pitched wheezes (musical sounds similar to a squeak). Crackles occur with the sudden opening of small airways that contain fluid, usually are heard during inspiration, and do not clear with a cough. Crackles resemble the sound of a lock of hair being rubbed between the thumb and forefinger and are heard in conditions such as pulmonary edema.</p>",
                        "id": "7417b55cc3cc49bfbc9b927e5312214c",
                        "videoIdContent": "51809063a6f35aec03596b02970a1bdf",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "471f7544e0fe43bd9753d2401b38aa33",
                                "content": "The stretch receptors in the lungs are irritated."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "23b36da87d5f4e96a116bffa19ea3291",
                                "content": "The diaphragm is weak and is difficult to move."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "1b6c7c16372949f68918cd7f2683e3cb",
                                "content": "This condition causes nerve endings to be especially sensitive."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "8f54e1ec30c04008a50f86e913259806",
                                "content": "The inflamed pleurae cannot glide against each other as they normally do."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "471f7544e0fe43bd9753d2401b38aa33",
                                    "content": "The stretch receptors in the lungs are irritated."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "23b36da87d5f4e96a116bffa19ea3291",
                                    "content": "The diaphragm is weak and is difficult to move."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "1b6c7c16372949f68918cd7f2683e3cb",
                                    "content": "This condition causes nerve endings to be especially sensitive."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
