                        "content": "A client who has been diagnosed with pleurisy tells the nurse that it is painful to inhale. The nurse responds that this is an expected finding because of which physical response to this disorder?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPleurisy is an inflammation of the visceral and parietal pleurae. The inflammation prevents the parietal and visceral pleural surfaces from gliding over each other with respiration. As a result, the client experiences pain, especially with inspiration. The remaining options are incorrect.",
                        "id": "863b193bcef348f186b6c804da9c39e5",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
